## Docs — etude-zcq (Changed: no)

No shipped docs needed. The change enriches the internal fetchBangAbort error (merge-base stderr) — a path
unreachable via real etude sync (a successful fetch downloads the new object, so merge-base resolves at
exit 0/1, never 128), exercised only by the new unit test. docs/sync.md documents fetch/push failures
generically ('fetch failed: ...' / 'push failed: ...') and the diverged-ref path verbatim; it does NOT
quote the abort message, so it stays accurate. No generated docs/CHANGELOG. (If the abort path ever
becomes user-facing, docs/sync.md 'Transport or local failures' is its natural home — deferred.)
